content.detailedDescription:
No ano de 2004, durante as ferias de julho eu estive com um grupo de amigos e meu irmao mais velho em um acampamento proximo a cidade de nova friburgo, br. em um dos dias, eu e meu irmao fomos escalados para fazer a honda noturna e alimentar a fogueira.. eu mesmo tive a iniciativa de dar uma volta e buscar lenhas.. eu me distanciei bem de onde estavamos, o local era bem aberto, bastante arvores e estava bem claro pois a lua estava linda. eu estive ao redor de algumas arvores, e andei mais um pouco.. nesse momento eu escutei um barulho como de algo que navega sob o espaço.. barulho bem suave e estranho, dai eu vi a coisa mais linda que ja vi em toda minha vida.. suas luzes acilavam por baixo como a aurora boreal.
ele subia e pairou a 30m de mim aproximadamento, como se solbesse que eu estava ali, e em uma velocidade inesplicavel ele se foi para sempre. contei ao meu irmao, e ele disse que eu estava assustado, nao levou a serio. desde entao, nunca comentei com ninguem. mas tenho certeza do que vi. foi isso. ate algum dia. abraços 
nicholas
content.summary: Estive em um acampamento, do qual estava com meu irmao e amigos.. vi sozinho durante a noite, em uma honda noturna... eu estava procurando lenha e vi o que tenho certeza que a coisa mais linda e estranha que ja vi. nunca contei a ninguem.

content.detailedDescription:
While sitting on my balcony at the hampton in orange beach, i notice the object moving east to west in a straight line at 10 pm.  it kept the same height and was moving at what appeared to be around 30-40 miles an hour.  it appeared to be a cluster of bright lights similar to a cluster of balloons.  it made no sound and did not waver in speed or height.
the sighting lasted approx. 10 minutes.  i was very nervous at seeing this and.  it continued west until i could not see it any longer.
i called 911 and reported what i saw.  i found out this morning that the 911 call was in foley, approx. 10 miles from the beach.  i called the police back this morning and no one else had reported anything at least to them.
i managed to get 3 iphone videos of it.  i have a dji phantom drone which has a 4k camera. i turned that on and tried to get a video of it but was unable to do so.
content.summary: Looked like a cluster of very bright balloons moving east to west over the gulf of mexico

content.detailedDescription:
October 1st 2015
surrey bc canda @ 20:42
clear sky

i went outside for a smoke with my husband at around 8:40, its completely dark out, no porch light on, nothing. i heard a plane, as i looked up to see the plane i noticed a curved line of lights floating/flying vertically the opposite directing of where the plane was headed. when i first saw it i thought it was just my eyes, i focused more on it,about 5 sec, by this time the plane was out of sight. 
it looked like a huge piece of clear plastic, almost as if it was shinning or it had a mirror like paint... (so hard to describe) with lights on the edge... as it was getting closer i couldn't see the "body" anymore, (it almost looked like it had a small dome on the top) now i could just see the small white lights on the edge of the object. i was in awe... i promptly asked my husband if he was seeing the same as me and he almost missed it! 
he saw it though, he took a good look at it for about 10 or 15 secs as we watched the lights get dimmer and dimmer. 
it became out of sight because of a tree and even though we tried to detect it again that was in vain. it was gone.
unfortunately my cellphone was inside the house, so i didn't take any pics nor recorded it. i couldn't stop staring at it. 
i don't know what to think of it but i know that wasn't "normal", i am a fan of the skies and i look up every time i can, i've never seen nor experienced nothing like it... 
i don't know what that was, but i'm not crazy!
content.summary: I saw a line of lights vertically flying horizontly. looked like i was looing at the side of a disc of some sort

content.detailedDescription: Was waiting for the bus when i noticed a strange object above me and my wife. flew near cloud level altitude,,  appearing star like,  solid in color,  orange,  red,  and white...Flying south,  coming from nearby mountains.. flew straight south,  sometimes zig zaging, then would stop and  hover,  while moving side to side, up and down, very quickly.  made no sound whatsoever,  and had pulsating lights that were probably going all around the object,  appearing boomerang shape after... after hovering for few minutes,  disappeared going straight up.. in a blink of an eye... when i thought it was over,,  object reappeared,,  coming the same way it did before,, did same manauvers,, and was gone... there were helicopters moving toward the object,,  maybe they saw it too, and a cesna kept circleling at higher elevation around the object at higher altitude.... clearly wasnt a helicopter nor plane...... took pictures of object which were not altered..... and keeping in mind drones were not common as they are now....
content.summary: Object appeared,, hover,  then start moving in eratic way, then disappear,,  then reappear and repeated....

content.detailedDescription: Was outside waiting on the dogs, saw a bright flash of light in the western sky out of the corner of my eye.  i turned that direction and thought is was an airplane but didn't see the normal steady flash of a commercial jet. when it flashed next, it was heading n.E.. the flash was much larger and brighter than any airplane i'd ever seen, that's what caught my eye.  it stayed on that course for approximately 4-5 flashes. the flashes were approximately 30-45 seconds apart. the distance this craft traveled between flashes varied. once it traveled approximately 3 times farther then it did between the last flashes. i noticed the red strobe from a commercial flight below it as the craft flashed. they were not close at all as i didn't see any reflection from the flash on the plane. that's when the flash turned north. this object didn't move as far between flashes as it headed north. i last saw it next to a star so i kept my eye on the star and the object stayed next to this star for approximately 4 flashes then moved s.E. at an angle past where it flew over the commercial plane then moved north again.  it went behind the trees and i lost track of it. i thought it odd that the flash was much brighter and larger than any commercial jet that was in the air at the time. i never heard any of the planes i saw fly over so i new they were high. the flash looked as if it was at a higher elevation than the commercial planes.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Bright flashing lights traveling in different directions and hovering.

content.detailedDescription: . my wife and i were sitting in back yard. the great allentown fair was going on. in allentown, pa.This object made no noise what so ever. we just happened to look up. sitting in back yard. great allentown fair going on across the street. surprised what we seen. grabbed cellphone to take pictures. we lost sight of object because out of sight range.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Looked up no noise seen bright light reflecting. sitting in back yard. great allentown fair was going on across the street

content.detailedDescription: I was driving south on ca hw 60.  a flash of light caught my eye in the sky, which appeared to be an elongated silver object.  at first glance i thought it was possibly an american airlines 767, which were shiny silver with stripes down the side, but then i noticed there were no stripes or distinguishable objects protruding from the craft, e.G. tail fin, jet engines, etc.  the object was flying south towards march air reserve base at a steady altitude, and as soon as it was about to be over the base, it disappeared.  i continued south onto ca hw 215 and as i drove past march air reserve base about 5 to 10 minutes later i saw two f-15s take off and shoot off in the direction the craft appeared to be going before it vanished.
content.summary: Silver diisc dissappear over march afp, two fighters sortied in same direction.

content.detailedDescription: This morning i had noticed that the clouds in the sky especially around the sun looked  stranger than they normally have been looking these days.  while on a stoplight (i had to wait for this like to change  three times before i was  able to make my left hand turn onto lagrange from 143rd st.)   i was looking up at the sky and noticed streaks of dark coming from the cloud cover where the sun was peeking through it almost looked like someone had taken a paintbrush and used it to create this effect.  also to the left of the cloud covering the sun there was a partial rainbow.  there are no rain clouds in the sky it is a pretty sunny day today and the sun is very bright.  my daughter loves rainbows and because of how peculiar the sky look today i figured i'd take a couple of snapshots. ( this light always takes  for ever to change)   after i got home i started looking at those pictures i had taken on my phone searching for the rainbow .  i didn't see a rainbow home but what i didn't scene was even more bizarre .  i even put the pictures up on my  big screen tv to see if i can get a better look at it because when i zoom in on these objects there is not much detail.   i had seen airplanes in the sky at this very same time you're not in my photos the were not  i focus.   i noticed that there were many black dark gray type spheres dots in the sky just above where the sun was shining if you zoom in to the blue sky  on these photos you'll see what i'm talking about .  i'm going to send you the original shots they should  you time and date stamped they were taken on an iphone 6 plus i'm wondering if you were able to enhance his picture somehow if there is more detail that may come out on these strange things in the sky.   it may be nothing but because there are so many and depending on where in the frame they are located they  look anywhere between dark almost black to light gray there's one or two or maybe even three in the cloud cover on the white clouds and then there are some that are in the blue sky as well take a look maybe you can figure out what they are because i'm stumped.  the sun was very bright so you were really not able to look on that direction for very long and that was while squinting. i'm guessing i might have seen these things with my bare eyes if i wore sunglasses.
content.summary: the sun was very bright and the cloud cover looked very odd but that has been the norm these days however today there seem to be dark streaks like a paintbrush coming up from around the sun and what seemed to be a piece of a rainbow  shined through.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i and four of our kids went to the country to watch the lunar eclipse. my 17 year old son, my husband and myself all watched a bright light move from the south to the north toward what we thought was a bright star above us. the bright light moved over the "star" and got brighter for about 3 seconds then the "star" moved to the side and disappeared. the bright light remained. it was like they were changing shifts or something.
content.summary: Bright light flew toward other bright light and took it's place in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I went outside this morning at 6:50 am to let the dogs do their morning business, something woke me up but not sure what but it was like i had to get up, looked up spotted the unusual object ran back in the house grabbed a cheap nikon camera i had taken about 20 shots only a few turned out the rest showed only a black screen when i loaded them on my pc.I always look at the skies, it is beautiful and relaxing and sometimes i spot things then before i realize i am just standing there in awe i run to find a phone or a camera and usually i miss getting a picture. this time i got pictures.It was white and shinny, it hoovered, then made some very quick moves kinda zig zagging i kept snapping pics because i wanted to catch the movement in sequence but when i loaded them only about 3 turned out the rest were black images, my feelings were it was not of this earth but i am not an expert in this, i just love to observe and learn, at first i thought it was just a very bright star until it moved around then i knew it wasn't , it did not look like any plane i have ever seen. and had 2 huge appendages out the top and a hook looking one to the side, i have never seen a plane like that, it reminded me of a cats ears except for the hook to the right.I lost sight when it zoomed quickly up ... straight up not on an angle like planes do. one things a few got this pink screen as well and i made no adjustments to my camera it really doesn't have many features just zoom in or out.
content.summary: 6:50 am e/s time not sure how long it was there before but i watched it from then until 7:24 then it zoomed off very fast like a flash

content.detailedDescription:
About 9:30pm i opened the rv door and looked up to night sky. the place was pitch black at nine mile canyon campground. i was only camper at cottonwood hollow. it was quiet and still.
stars out, clear sky. i looked along the ridge about 200  feet away, which was a steep canyon and noticed the object.
the hair on my neck stood up. felt electricity. it appeared to be looking directly at me. it hovered silently about 20' above the ridge. it must have been 4-12 feet wide. it was oval with flat sides. what could it be doing out in the middle of nowhere?
it was dark and had 3-5 lights arranged in a horizontal centered on shape. one light was red and others  were white. with the precision of a hummingbird the object suddenly zipped off behind the ridge out of my sight. i was hoping this was a drone. perhaps a corporate security drone, or a surveillance drone for government. i'd like to know if any other reports coming in from nine mile canyon. if there is any more information about this i'd like to know.
what i saw was real. i was not under any influences of alcohol or drugs. i was alert and seeing a ufo. please let me know what that was!!! i took a few pictures the next morning. slept very little in case i needed to defend myself. i'm concerned about the stare down i had with it.
could that have effected me somehow?! i seem to be ok now...
photo was taken next morning to show ridge.
content.summary: Opened door to rv. looked up at hilltop. hovering above outline of hilltop(80' above my campsite, 20' above hill was object,had 3-4 lights, one red, hovered for 30-40 seconds then zipped away

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting in my house and i heard an airplane so i went outside to see if i could see it. as i was searching the sky i saw a light that i first thought was in the woods but as i got to looking it was right above the tree line moving way to slow to be any type of aircraft or helicopter and it didnt make any sound at all!! it was a roundish sphere/orb that i would say was maybe the size of a big beach-ball, it was a orangish/amber color moving at a slow steady pace above the tree line. it basically came directly over my head from the northeast traveling diagonally to the southwest. i couldnt believe what i was seeing and basically stood there and watched with my jaw dropped until it finally disappeared over the tree line.
content.summary: Heard an airplane, went outside, saw this amber/orange glowing orb moving very slow above the tree line

content.detailedDescription: It was around 0850 pm on the 1st of october 2015. i walked out into the back yard to walk my dog and i looked up in the sky looking for the moon. i didn't see any moon but noticed a large number of lights moving across the night sky. there were about 15-20 dull white lights in a boomerang shape that were traversing the sky from a n to se direction. the craft was difficult to see, almost translucent but the lights were unmistakable. the lights did not blink and the craft made no noise. from what i could tell the craft was massive. it would have been between 3-4 full moons from front to back and roughly the same from side to side. the sky was clear and it took about 45-60 seconds for the craft to disappear. it was flying towards the atlantic ocean. i was awstruck as i saw the craft. i tried to get my wife to come out to see this thing but by the time she got there it was too far away to make out. we have airplanes and helicopters fly overhead quite often and this object could never be confused with either of these.
content.summary: Massive boomerang shaped ufo with 15-20 solid lights flying overhead in a north to southeast direction.

content.detailedDescription:
when i was around 6 yrs (1976) the family lived outside eustis, fla. we were moving and the house was empty of furniture, and as a kid thing me and my brother, a year younger, were spending the night sleeping in our sleeping bags in mom and dad's bedroom. we slept at the end of the bedroom that had a sliding glass door opening onto small deck. since the ground dropped away to a small lake, the deck was elevated about 5 feet off the ground.
  down the ground sloaped to the small lake then the ground rose back up on the other side. a road ran from right to left on the high ground across the lake. i woke up just in time to see what i thought was an ambulance emerging on the road to the right from some trees. i was flashing like aan ambulance and proceeded to move straight from left to right along to road across the lake. where a small dirt road runs from that road to the lake used by fishermen to put in boats, it turned in and followed the road down to the lake. i noticed that under all these flashing lights was a solid object casting a small shadow directly under neath. red and white lights flashing like crazy it came to where the dirt road hits the lake and i figured it was some guy putting his boat in (at maybe 3 am or so) it proceeded to cross the lake moving a few feet above the water and making no sound. when it hit the shore it glided up to that deck, just off the corner off it. it flashed red and whit light a a brilliant white light that was unreal. 
  i got up off the floor and started to walk to the glass door, saw my little brother sleeping on the floor next to me, and noticed that the object was shaped like a 10-12 foot tall dull lead kind of top. i got up and walked to it and the next thing i know it's the next morning.
  the next morning were siting at the breakfast table and i said to my parents "did you see the aliens land on the lawn last night?". they laughed and i was kind of ticked they didn't believe me.
  that night my brother and i were sleeping back in our bed room still on the floor, and i woke up real late early in the morning and i noticed a brilliant light out side the the window. sitiing on the floor i turned to wake my brother and show him the light but i couldn't wake him and he was stretched out super taught with his mouth stretched wide open and so were his eye and he couldn't/wouldn't close them that is all i remember.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Landed in front of me when a 6 yrish boy.

content.detailedDescription:
To start things off, i am only a 14 year old, i don't really wish to try and make up a fake story, especially since after today i am slightly creeped out.
at around 7:39 i was with my brother preparing for our halloween horror movie marathon. while watching the movie, i got up to get a cup of ice water and looked outside, which is a natural thing that i usually do. i noticed 3 lights in the sky flying in a triangular formation. i've seen many planes here, and there lights didn't look like any plane i've ever seen before. because it was cloudy outside(making the night sky gray) i was able to make out a black outline, however i cannot be certain since it was only there for about 9 or 10 seconds and i was to interested in the lights outside. when i first saw it, i didn't really have any thoughts of what it belonged to, so i looked up "3 lights in a triangular formation in the sky" and it came up with a bunch of information on ufo's. i was slightly duds turned by this, but i then returned to watch the movie. i should have noticed my cats strange behavior of running back and forth but i was focused on the movie more. when it was time for me to sleep, i decided to just go on my phone and browse a bit. i heard a high pitched humming sound from outside, but at the same time it wasn't loud at all. i looked outside and saw that the 3 dots were passing by again, but this time they were closer. i only got a glimpse of it for 5 seconds though since there were trees in the way. i don't know anything about aliens or ufos, and it could just be an airplane of some sort, but i still think it's best to ask for some answers then to be afraid of what i saw
thank you.

ps i all so includes a picture i found of triangular light thingys
content.summary: 3 lights forming a triangle in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I live in stoke-on-trent near two flight paths and am very used to the sight of planes but monday was strange, i stepped outside for a cigarette at 21.45 and as soon as i did i noticed a bright light in the north east sky i immediately knew it was not a plane so i turned to ask my girlfriend to please fetch my phone and as i turned around in the sky right above my house a triangle craft was just passing over, i would describe the craft as approximately 80-150 feet across with 3 corner lights and a round hollowed light in the middle, i also caught a very small glimpse of almost mayan looking markings on the underside of the craft, the craft made no sound whatsoever which i immediately noticed as it was only approximately 150 feet above my house, the craft was visible only for approximately 15 seconds at the most, the craft was on a north west to south east direction flight path, then the first object that had cought my attention passed over and i could now see it was not a plane but looked man made and it was definitely following the craft at a diatance.
content.summary: Triangle ufo 3 lights on corners and 1 in the middle with possible mayan markings

content.detailedDescription: At 20:15 hrs i was at work walking a parking platform with a good view of the sacramento sky line.I was waching flight path of planes flying nw out of sac international flying  east over mts,when i thought i saw a flash of light from other aircraft.I then spotted a  faint green light movin from nw to se,then i thought i saw a flash of light agin to corner of my eye,i lost track of faint green light whitch i think was a satellite.I saw light agin and fixated on that area of sky,only to to see a bright split sec flash of white light then  it would go out black. then it would light back up to a light 2 sec glow. with each flash it would move.Then saw a 747 out of s.F pass by going north. onec plane past by it light up for a splite sec and started to move into planes jet wash and taill 747.The flashing lasted 25 to 30 min untill it left be hind 747.
content.summary: Bright  split seconded white flash with 2 sec light glow.

content.detailedDescription: Sept 27th at around 10:00pm i was observing the red blood moon with and without my binoculars in my parking lot. one of my neighbors was walking his dog in the parking lot also and we were talking about the moon. all of a sudden there were 2 bright orange lights coming from the south. what caught my eye is the orange lights were very bright not like plane lights which i'm familiar with because i live next to ohare airport in park ridge, il. also what caught my eye was that they were flying parallel to each other maybe about 100-200 yards apart from each other. i thought for a moment maybe they were fighter jets the kind that fly in air shows. but then i noticed the orange light on the right  had hesitation erratic moves not like a steady flight pattern. then the one orange light on the left was trying to keep up with the orange light on the right. then they were trying to keep up with each other at the same speed. when i first noticed the 2 orange lights in the far distance it looked like the were going the same speed but when they got closer the were changing speeds to keep up with each other while still traveling parallel  to each other. at that point my guess was they weren't airplanes. i ran from my parking lot to my patio to get my binoculars. i still could see the 2 orange lights from my patio but due to there path my building started to block my view. so i ran back to the parking lot to still see if i could still observe the 2 orange lights but 1 light was gone and  the other was still traveling south. by then i had my binoculars and saw the object with my binoculars. it was a bright orange ball with a brighter white light towards the center. it was traveling very fast and it was hard to keep up with it while looking through my binoculars. then i decided not to use my binoculars and just observe it with the naked eye because of its speed. then it started to flicker out then disappear. i noticed a small white trail after it had disappeared. a part of me says they were some kind of flares but at the same time what confuses me is that they were traveling parallel to each other and also the movements and speed that they were traveling at raises my curiosity. what were they?
content.summary: While observing the red moon on sept 27th 2 orange objects  came from the south going north. near ohare aiirport.

content.detailedDescription: I was at a child's birthday party at a suburban community south of wilmington, de. as i walked toward my automobile, parked along the street, i noticed a bright and pulsating light to my left about 1 mile away and at about 40 degrees above the tree line. the object was pulsating and changing color from blue to white to red to orange in a pattern that made it seem to be rotating. it moved slowly with no derivation from its course and moved away from my position toward the north. i had no idea what this object was and called it to my wife's attention. i told her that i thought it was a ufo. i was excited by the object's presence and immediately ask my wife for her cell phone. i was able to activate the camera and filmed the object for a brief time. i was only able to magnify the picture near the middle of the sighting and the video is at some points shaky. the object continued to move away from me a disappeared behind the tree line near the horizon.
content.summary: I saw this object low in the sky just before dark when walking to my car.

content.detailedDescription: It was 6am at work while approaching post i scanned area before taking over.While scanning i spotted to my left what looked like a star after taking over i took a closer look thru binoculars,and what i observed was no star.It was mattalic and best i can describe it as was a chrome rounded cone shape craft.I called supervision and reported what i saw, and they came to my location and wittnesed the object themselves.At least 5 others saw the object before sounding the alarm. it hung in the area for 3hrs before loosing sight.Photography is not allowed on site.
content.summary: At nuclear power plant spotted star like object. looked thru binoculars at object. it was not a star. reported to supervision.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from work (i was enlisted in the army at the time, roughly july of 1997, a generator and vehicle mechanic with a secret clearance and had earned multiple awards/recognition's) when driving down the road, i noticed multiple lights that were pulsating at odd/irregular intervals.  upon coming to an intersection, i stopped, shut my car off and got out to look at the lights.  there was barely enough sunlight for me to drive without using my headlights.  i stared at the lights, thinking they were army helicopters (blackhawks, quite common at fort drum, ny at the time), but there weren't any flashing lights (red/green to indicate direction of aircraft), they were to close to be flying in any type of formation, and there was absolutely no noise.  if they were indeed helicopters, i would've heard the engines (as there was between 3-8 lights pulsating on and off in a "v" shape, staying in the "v" shape the entire time, and i was close enough that i would've heard a single helicopter engine, even a smaller one like that of an oh-58 series).  i thought that they might be flares from soldiers doing a field exercise, but flares when launched, will slowly float to the ground, and are a bright white - these lights maintained their altitude.  they weren't planes...Again, no noise and not red/green lights.  besides that, the "v" shaped (which was a very wide "v") object moved slowly, seemed to stop, turn a little, move slowly, turn a little, move forward.  i swear that it moved towards me, stopped, turned directly to me, made all of it's lights glow, then ascended slowly, as if it saw me and was just slowly "sneaking" away, and disappeared.  while i couldn't see any specifics of the object itself (exact color, texture, windows, markings etc.), i could barely make out the outline of the front of it.  it had to be at least 300 feet side to side, if not more.  simply put - i was in awe over seeing it, and not being able to tell what it was.  i knew it was a ufo, as there was/is no other explanation for something that size, moving like it did, and not making any noise at all.  after doing a lot of reading/research, i've learned that military bases are frequently visited by ufo's, which is why, some 18 years later, i've decided to share this with mufon.  hopefully, someone will be able to collaborate this sighting.  i'll include screen shots of google maps depicting where i was, where the ufo was, and the direction that the ufo was heading.  the object i saw was nearly identical to the "v" shaped ufo over phoenix in march of 1997.  of course, i didn't realize that until years later, thanks to google images when i googled "v shaped ufo", and it came up with a picture and a caption. i'm a professional photographer now, and still have my secret clearance.  and no, i'm not crazy.
content.summary: Huge "v" shaped, dark w/glowing/pulsating lights-no noise whatsoever

content.detailedDescription:
While viewing the super moon eclipse est time 21:35 cdt, i noticed two spheres(slightly smaller than a basketball in appearance) traveling from se to ne at an extreme rate of speed.  they appeared to fade or collapse before they disappeared from sight.  approximately 45 seconds later i saw a second sphere slightly larger than a basketball in appearance on the same trajectory and about the same speed with the same characteristics.  the light was extremely bright and orange  the incident was also witnessed by may neighbor and his 9 year old son (who brought the first objects to my attention).  i am on a landing approach to the des moines international airport and i can approximate the speed of landing aircraft.  the speed of these objects i would estimate as 7-10 times faster than a landing aircraft.  they glowed steady without sound or strobes like you would find on a conventional aircraft.  size and distance was hard to determine since the sky was clear and they were higher than surrounding structures.

the objects were very similar to objects my wife and i saw over the atlantic ocean at myrtle beach sc in 2008.
content.summary: Bright glowing orange spheres  high rate of speed

content.detailedDescription: I was on my way home from taking my daughter to school when i noticed a beautiful rainbow colored cloud over the mountain range. so when i pulled into my driveway i decided to take a picture of it. i honestly did not see the object in question at that time. two days later i was looking through my pictures and noticed a small blemish on the picture i had taken. i zoomed in on it and started freaking out at what i saw. so i did not actually witness the object but did get it in a photo. the object in question is about three quarters of the way from left to right and about center from top to bottom of the photo.
content.summary: I took a picture of the view from my driveway and noticed a strange object in the photo.

content.detailedDescription: This photo was taken in grand canyon national park in the area called hopi point. i never saw the object, i was trying to capture the storm that was developing in the middle of the canyon. at night i was reviewing the pictures and i was surprised to see the object there. it could be a bird, but a big one apparently, there wasn't airplanes sounds. the picture was taken with a samsung galaxi note 4 smart phone
content.summary: I was taking pictures of the landscape and the storm in the middle of the canyon
